    ## Implementing chained comparisons in Ruby

    (1..10).each do |x|
      case
      when x < 3
        puts "#{x} is quite low"
      when 3 <= x < 6
        puts "#{x} is quite all right"
      when 6 <= x < 10
        puts "#{x} is quite fine"
      when 10 <= x
        puts "#{x} is quite high"
      end
    end


